added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: Costume Contest
added.description: Sick of losing the costume contest to the Hive Five every year, the Titans hatch a scheme to win.

added.title: Monster Squad!
added.description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

added.title: 50% Chad
added.description: Having grown tired of their current villains, the Titans hold an audition for a new arch nemesis.

added.title: The Score
added.description: The Titans have a hard time dealing with their emotions when an evil composer changes the music in their show.

added.title: The Ghost
added.description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Gumball experiences an impossibly unfortunate chain of events.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Mirror
added.description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

added.title: The Ghouls
added.description: It's Halloween in Elmore. As the kids go trick or treating we see what everyone in town is up to. The ghosts and ghouls are finding it increasingly difficult to scare children, and are only scaring part-time. Can Gumball and Darwin help them get their scare back?

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Trick or Creek
added.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

added.title: The Legend of the Library
added.description: When the library is thrown into disarray, an ancient ghost is awoken.

added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: Ghoul Spirit
added.description: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.

added.title: Gwen Scary, Gwen Lost
added.description: When Chef discovers his spooky Halloween pranks have never scared the kids he's devastated. Determined to get them this year, he agrees to hand over full control of his pranking to Gwen. Her plan turns out far spookier then Chef ever hoped.

added.title: Wiggin' Out
added.description: Bridgette donates her hair to a charity that makes wigs for hairless cats and now some classmates want to do the same. But their quest for perfect wig hair drives them to weird and dangerous lengths.

added.title: The Upside of Hunger
added.description: Owen has a mishap while baking an upside-down cake and is transported to an upside-down world where he is forced to outwit himself in order to get his cake back.

added.title: Duncan Carving
added.description: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

added.title: Omelettes Are Forever
added.description: The gang gets caught up in international espionage and intrigue when they cross paths with British secret agent, Jenny Vex, and must help her complete her dangerous mission of stopping a monstrous, evil mercenary called Minus from killing the meal of breakfast - forever.

added.title: Ghost in the Mystery Machine
added.description: Fred's worst nightmare comes true when an evil spirit possesses the Mystery Machine and turns his beloved van into an unrelenting monster out to destroy him and the gang before they can solve the mystery.

added.title: Naughty or Ice
added.description: Daphne brings the gang to a fancy Ice Hotel co-owned by her family where a new exhibit of ice age artifacts is opening. Things heat up, however, when a frozen Ice Man thaws out and goes on a rampage inside the hotel. Solving the mystery becomes even more complicated when the gang realizes Daphne may just have ulterior motives for going to the hotel to begin with.

added.title: Night of the Upsetting Shorts
added.description: The gang heads to Shaggy's beloved grandmother's Florida retirement home, where they learn a crazed Ape Man has been frightening the elderly residents. In order to lessen Shaggy's worry that he doesn't give his Grammy enough bragging rights, the gang pretends Shaggy is their leader and Daphne, his adoring girlfriend, inadvertently putting more pressure on Shaggy to solve the mystery of the Ape Man - who, as it turns out, is less horrifying than the shorts Fred decided to wear to beat the Florida heat.

added.title: Junkyard Dogs
added.description: Scooby Doo runs into an old kennel mate from the rescue shelter, Axel, who is now a state-of-the-art, highly trained K-9 police dog. Axel's patronizing attitude towards Scooby makes him and Shaggy determined to be the ones who solve the mystery of the Trash Monster that's been attacking locals at the garbage dump. Meanwhile, in an attempt to better understand Fred, Daphne "becomes" Fred for the day, much to Fred's delight - at first.

added.title: One Minute Mysteries!
added.description: Scooby and Shaggy love hanging out with their very best eating buddy, Barry Allen aka the Flash. Barry is sad his two buddies always get pulled away from their food-fests to go solve mysteries. He decides to help our Mystery Solvers by solving their mysteries Flash-style so quickly our gang can't keep up. Our gang love and respect the Flash but they have a very specific way they like to solve mysteries.

added.title: Hollywood Knights!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are investigating one of the most haunted mansions in the historic Hollywood Hills, they meet up with none-other than famous actor George Takei. His house is next door, and he's hoping to save this abandoned, old mansion as a historic landmark. As an old suit of armor comes alive and chases them all over the spooky estate, the gang and Mr. Takei discover the mansion is not as abandoned as everyone thought.

added.title: The New York Underground!
added.description: Our Shaggy is a bit of a Beatnik poet, and Scooby is so proud that he enters Shaggy into a poetry slam contest in Central Park. But when Shaggy finds out he's going up against famous singer-songwriter Halsey, he just about freaks. He freaks even more when the poetry slam is attacked by a horrible gator-man-monster from the New York City sewers below!

added.title: Fear of the Fire Beast!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are in Sicily, they're chasing a fire monster! But, they are surprised to meet up with none other than famous actor Steve Buscemi. His ancestors are from this area, and he has a lot of cousins in town and was just visiting. But, he's being plagued by fire monster attacks. Our gang teams up with Mr. Buscemi to get to the bottom of this fiery mystery. Let's hope Mr. Buscemi can train our gang to be proper fire fighters and mystery solvers, before they all get burned.

added.title: Too Many Dummies!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are hired to escort a supposedly possessed ventriloquist dummy to the annual Ventriloquist Talent Competition, they meet up with the two judges of the competition, Jeff Dunham and Darci Lynne Farmer. True to form, the supposedly possessed dummy turns out to be terribly-and-horribly-possessed! It comes alive and attacks the competition!

added.title: Nowhere to Hyde
added.description: The gang follows a mysterious figure through a marsh to the house of a latter-day Dr. Jekyll, whose alter ego is apparently a jewel thief.

added.title: Mystery Mask Mix-Up
added.description: When Daphne innocently buys a mask that once belonged to an ancient warlord, the gang finds itself pursued by zombies and ghosts.

added.title: Jeepers It's the Creeper
added.description: The kids look for a ghostly bank robber, who seems able to walk through walls.

added.title: A Night of Fright Is No Delight
added.description: Scooby must spend the night in a haunted house in order to receive an inheritance.

added.title: That's Snow Ghost
added.description: A ski trip turns spooky for the gang when they run into the ghostly Yeti Beast and a Tibetan hermit, who says he is responsible for summoning the monster.

added.title: The Horrible Herd
added.description: A heard of supernatural skull cattle wreak havoc on Crystal Cove.

added.title: Dance of the Undead
added.description: When Crystal Cove's favorite southern celebrity chef has a cooking accident, strange incidents ensue.

added.title: The Devouring
added.description: When a Gluten Demon rises up and attacks famous foodie Francilee Jackson, our gang has to try to stop this monster before it consumes all the bread, pasta and other tasty foodstuffs in Crystal Cove.

added.title: Stand and Deliver
added.description: A dandy, well-groomed, 18th century Englishman haunts the highways of Crystal Cove.

added.title: The Man in the Mirror
added.description: In the basement of a local haunted mansion, the gang finds a strange mirror with a mind of its own.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park V
added.description: The fifth installment of Terror Tales finds Benson trying to spice up the park's annual Halloween party by renting a wish making machine.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park IV
added.description: The park guys try to keep Muscle Man awake with scary stories on a long drive so that they can meet his mom.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park III
added.description: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park II
added.description: The park can be a very scary place at night.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park
added.description: The park can be a very scary place at night.

added.title: Fool Moon
added.description: Strange things start happening when Uncle Grandpa installs a moon roof in the RV.

added.title: Afraid of the Dark
added.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

added.title: Trick or Threat
added.description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

added.title: Haunted RV
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa's Haunted House spirals out of control, the gang must save the teenagers stuck inside.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System, the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: Clown College
added.description: While tailgating at a State U. homecoming football game, Ben teams up with Grandpa Max's old college buddies to keep the crazy clown Zombozo from robbing the stadium blind at halftime.

added.title: Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max meet a family that appears to be a mirror image of them, but when Max goes off on a hike with their matriarch, Maxine, Ben is forced to babysit Simon Sez, a brat with a Billy Billions designed backpack  that turns him into a formidable robot.

added.title: Something I Ate
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max go on a tour of the impervious Fort Knox, but when Dr. Animo sicks a hungry ani-mutate on the Fort, Ben must stop it before it gobbles up the nation's monitory standard!

added.title: Steam is the Word
added.description: In the heart of Silicon Valley, Ben has to stop Victorian villain Steam Smythe from securing an epic power source sealed in a Tesla time capsule.

added.title: The Beast Inside
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Max make a return to Max's alma mater but this time it's no homecoming. Dr. Animo has made a scary transformation and found a way to release the very dangerous animal nature of humans, including Max's life-long friend!

added.title: Truth
added.description: An old Plumber partner of Max's resurfaces with nefarious intentions and ends up stealing the dangerous Null Void Projector.

added.title: Big Tick
added.description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he's too short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: The Trouble with Truth
added.description: The JLA find themselves in danger of losing Wonder Woman when the goddess Athena comes to Earth with an offer Diana can't refuse, filling the position of the Goddess of Truth on Mt. Olympus.

added.title: Double Cross
added.description: Batman has Plastic Man disguise himself as Two-Face in order to set a trap for Deadshot. Unfortunately things get complicated when the real Two-Face escapes custody.

added.title: Battle for the Bottled City
added.description: Atom shrinks Superman so he can visit his fellow Kryptonians in the bottled city of Kandor. Soon after, Brainiac attacks and takes off with the bottle. Atom is forced to take control of one of Superman's damaged robots in order to follow after Brainiac and retrieve the city.

added.title: The Glitch
added.description: In order to stop Unagami the ninja must obtain three Key-tanas, the first of which is hidden in the game zone Terra Kerana, one of Prime Empire's most dangerous game environments.

added.title: The Cliffs of Hysteria
added.description: While being chased by Unagami's dreaded Red Visors the ninja must climb the 'Cliffs of Hysteria', however, they make a startling discovery: Unagami is converting players into energy cubes in order to build a portal into the real world!

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: The Eclipse/Follow Haavik!
added.description: There's an eclipse happening over Los Volmos, but there's something even more strange going on. Dan and Drago quickly realize something's up; no one seems like themselves today. The two need to get to the bottom of it and return things back to normal./ Magnus and Ajit spot Haavik on the street and decide to follow him, but the shape shifting Haavik is on to them. It's not long before an epic brawl breaks out between them - Five Faction Fusion Sabrus vs. Nillious X Darkus and Pharol.

added.title: Tiko's Back?!/Arise, Ultimate Infinity!
added.description: Tiko's Back?!: In order to make Sabrus a 6 faction fusion Bakugan, Haavik heads into the maze to try to capture a golden Bakugan who has brought "mayhem and destruction" to Earth once before - Tiko!/Arise, Ultimate Infinity!: The Awesome Brawlers manage to thwart Haavik's attempt to fuse Tiko with Sabrus, but Haavik ends up escaping with the golden Bakugan, Pyravian. Now the Awesome Brawlers must track down Haavik before he can form his ultimate 6 faction fusion Bakugan.

added.title: The AB Bakugan Battle League!
added.description: With all the mayhem and destruction Haavik is causing, the Awesome Brawlers decide that a bit of Bakugan brawling is the perfect distraction to take their minds off all the trouble. With the help of some friends, they start the Awesome Brawler Bakugan Battle league!/ The Awesome Brawler's Bakugan Battle league rages on. Just as the semifinal round comes to a close, an uninvited guest crashes the party, bringing an alarming end to the battle league.

added.title: Haavik's Challenge/Storm Haavik's Tower
added.description: Haavik's Challenge: Haavik has crashed the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan League, and challenges the Awesome Brawlers in a battle league of his own!/ Storm Haavik's Tower: In order to keep Earth and Vestroia safe and rescue Drago, the Awesome Brawlers agree to enter Haavik's Bakugan Battle League, and race toward Haavik's tower for the final showdown.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik/Their Fights
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik: Dan and the Awesome brawlers have made their way up Haavik's tower as the final showdown between Haavik and the Awesome Brawlers begins./Their Fights: Haavik's Bakugan battle league rages on in an ultimate showdown between the Awesome Brawlers, vs Haavik and his destructive friends.

added.title: Halloween En El Arroyo
added.description: Llegó Halloween al bosque, y Craig se embarca en una misión para recolectar la mayor cantidad de dulces como sea humanamente posible. Pero un espíritu aterrador del pasado del bosque amenaza su botín.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Falla
added.description: Para detener a Unagami, los Ninjas debe obtener 3 Keytanas, la primera está escondida en Tierra Karana, uno de los entornos de juego más peligrosos.

added.title: Los Acantilados de la Histeria
added.description: Los Ninjas suben a los Acantilados de la histeria y descubren que Unagami convierte a los jugadores en cubos de energía para construir un portal.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: La casa de munecas embrujada
added.description: Craig y sus amigos descubren que los persigue una muñeca aterradora y su casa de muñecas embrujada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Escuela De Payasos
added.description: Mientras Ben disfruta en el estacionamiento a la salida de un partido de fútbol americano de ex estudiantes de la Universidad de State, se alía con los antiguos compañeros del Abuelo Max para impedir que Zombozo, un payaso demente, le robe a todo el público durante el entretiempo.

added.title: Aventuras Cuidando Ninos
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max se encuentran con una familia que parece ser un reflejo de ellos. Pero cuando Max sale a caminar con su matriarca, Maxine, Ben se ve obligado a cuidar a Simon Sez, un malcriado con una mochila diseñada por Billy Billones, que lo convierte en un robot formidable.

added.title: Algo Que Comi
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max van de paseo al impenetrable Fort Knox, pero cuando el Doctor Ánimo hace que un animal-mutante hambriento se enferme, iBen debe detenerlo antes de que se devore la reserva monetaria de la nación!

added.title: Vapor Es La Palabra
added.description: En el corazón de Silicon Valley, Ben debe impedir que Vapor Smythe, el villano victoriano, consiga una fuente de poder épica sellada en una cápsula del tiempo diseñada por Tesla.

added.title: La Bestia Interior
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max regresan a la universidad de Max, pero esta vez no les dan una cálida bienvenida. El Doctor Ánimo ha hecho una transformación escalofriante y ha descubierto un modo de liberar la peligrosa naturaleza animal de los seres humanos...iincluida la del amigo de toda la vida de Max!

added.title: Three Cheers for Cheer
added.description: When hard-working Cheer exhausts her crew running a string of drills to protect a Whiffle orchard from possible emergencies, Share's belly badge accidentally creates two Cheer duplicates. Cheer takes a recreation break, unaware that her clones are working Share and the crew - who think they're the real Cheer - even harder.

added.title: The Badge of Courage
added.description: When Dibble dresses up as a superhero complete with a pretend belly badge, the Whiffles think she's the real thing and need her to confront an imaginary monster that they believe lives in a cave. She bravely enters the cave but loses her courage when she loses the belly badge, until Funshine convinces her that her bravery came from inside her.

added.title: One Wise Bear
added.description: The Bears become lost in the Valley of Whispering Winds, where voices whisper in their ears and make them lose faith in themselves. Racing to their rescue, Tenderheart leads them to the only one who knows the antidote to the words of the Winds: a mysterious old bear of great wisdom who teaches them a valuable lesson about listening to your heart.

added.title: Hide and Sneak
added.description: Dibble is chosen as "It" in a Whiffle game of Hide-and-Seek. The game turns serious when Bluster traps the Bears inside the Cloudseeker. Dibble and Cheer must find the Whiffles and free her friends.

added.title: Dibble's Dust-Up
added.description: Grumpy's determination to get the Cloudseeker clean is comically thwarted when Dibble befriends a stowaway trio of cute dust bunnies.

added.title: The Dolly Vanishes
added.description: On an overnight train trip to visit Floyd at college, Lola's doll vanishes. Baby Bugs acts as a detective as he tries to solve the missing Edna mystery via a series of simple flashbacks, seen from each Baby Looney Tunes' point of view.

added.title: There's Nothing Like a Good Book
added.description: A nagging question regarding the composition of the moon brings the Baby Looney Tunes to experience their very first visit to the library.

added.title: A Turtle Named Mrytle
added.description: A trip to the seashore brings the Baby Looney Tunes into contact with a just-hatched turtle that Melissa, apart from the rest because of her bossy attitude, names Myrtle. Melissa just loves little Myrtle and wants to keep her from walking into the ocean so she may take Myrtyle home for herself.

added.title: Duck's Reflucks
added.description: Baby Daffy has Baby Bugs right where he wants him, as the subject of his digital photography and at the mercy of his endless, egocentric creative whims.

added.title: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes explore a world of botanic wonder as they search for just the right spot to plant a young lemon tree.
